descript.abstract: This data set contains land cover polygons and associated attributes. From 1999 to 2003 land cover boundaries were created by interpreting, delineating, and digitizing vegetation communities and impervious surfaces. The Minnesota Land Cover Classification System (MLCCS)was used to interpret land cover types. MN DNR color infrared photography, Dakota County digital color aerial photography, and Pictometry were used for interpreting vegetation along with the following GIS data sets: national wetland inventory, county biological survey, hydric soils, physical water features, fieldline boundaries, woodline boundaries, and contours. Land cover boundaries were delineated on 1997 Metropolitan Council Digital Ortho Quarter Quads (DOQQ'S) from 1999 to 2000 (1991 United States Geological Survey DOQQ's were used for high water areas that were flooded on the 1997 DOQQ's), on 2000 Metropolitan Council DOQQ's from 2000 to 2002 and on 2002 Dakota County DOQQ's during 2003. Resulting interpreted and delineated land cover polygons were field checked where visible or accessible from roads or public property. Polygon boundaries were then digitized in ArcInfo at a 1:3,000 scale. A Minumum mapping unit of 1 acre was observed for both built-up and semi-natural and natural polygons. Exceptions: feedlots, prairies, stormwater ponds, and many wetlands were mapped at smaller sizes, and a portion of the City of Eagan extending from the southern municipal boundary northwest to 35E and east to Dodd Road to the north and Highway 3 to the south was re-mapped at a 1/4 acre mmu (only MLCCS 10,000 level codes). Partial updates were completed for: many wetland basins within the Vermillion River Watershed (political boundary) in 2006-07 during the WWIA using 2005 and 2006 aerial photography, many wetland basins within the North Cannon River Watershed (poltical boundary) in 2007-08 during the WWIA using 2006 and 2008 aerial photography, the entire Vermillion River Watershed (political boundary) in 2009 using 2008 and 2009 aerial photography, a 1 mile buffer area of both sides of all waterways within the North Cannon River Watershed (political boundary) in 2010 using 2009 aerial photography, all remaining sections of the North Cannon River Watershed (political boundary) in early 2012 using 2011 aerial photography, many areas of Dakota County north of Apple Valley/Rosemount during 2012 using 2011 aerial photography while spot checking data, all Dakota County FNAP property easements through 2013, and all BWSR approved Wetland Banks in Dakota County through 2013.
descript.purpose: Natural Resource Inventory developed county-wide using Minnesota DNR's Minnesota Land Cover Classification System (MLCCS) to accurately describe natural, semi-natural, and non-natural vegetative communities in Dakota County. Data can be used to measure levels of impervious surfaces, inventory wetlands, analyze greenways, evalauate land cover, and identify ecological communities. The database is vital to supporting SWCD conservation practices in Dakota County, Dakota County's Farmland and Natural Area Program (FNAP) and local wetland inventory assessments.

attr.attrdef: Final land cover code as 5 digit number. This field will duplicate the most accurate land cover code for each polygon - either field visit (fld_code) or remote sensing (img_code). Mandatory.
Final land cover code in alphanumeric format. The alphanumeric code equivalent to C_NUM. Automatically populated with MLCCS tools.
Final land cover code as a text description. Automatically populated with MLCCS tools.

Land cover code derived from field work. The land cover code derived from field interpretation. Can be applied to any land cover type. Must be present if invasive species or natural quality modifiers are used.
Date of field work (year-month-day with no delimiters, e.g. 20043019).

Field check level (from the Field Check Form in the manual). The degree the polygon was field visited: 0 = site not visited 1 = viewed from distance 2 = visited edge of site 3 = visited part of site 4 = visited entire site
See manual page for details. Mandatory if FLD_CODE is populated.

Land cover code derived from aerial photo or image interpretation. The land cover code derived by remote sensing, typically using aerial photos. Several images can be used in concert. Not mandatory if land cover of site initially interpreted from field work.

List of date and type of images, e.g. [2003 FSA color DOQ |2000 Met Council BW DOQ]. List the most current image first, descending in chronological order. Use "yyyy source and image type" with a "|" pipe as delimiters. Standard entries:
2011 Dakota County Pictometry 2011 Dakota County DOQ 2008 Dakota County DOQ 2003 FSA color DOQ 2000 Met Council BW DOQ 1994 DNR CIR

Modifiers for percent imperviousness, 000 = 0% to 100%. Valid values are 000 to 100.
012 - 12% impervious (2 acre lot) 025 - 25% impervious (2 acre lot) 038 - 38% impervious (1/4 acre lot)

Modifiers for cultural land use. Valid values are 210 to 276.
210 - Residential 211 - Low Density Residential (one dwelling per acre) 212 - Medium Density Residential (2-5 per acre) 213 - High Density Residential (> 5 per acre)
220 - commercial/industrial 226 - recreational 227 - utility 228 - brownfield 229 - other
230 - transportation (roads/railroads) 231 - roads 232 - railroads 233 - parking lot 234 - runway 235 - marina
240 - open space 241 - parks 242 - golf course 245 - cemetery
250 - pavement
260 - farm buildings 261 - farmstead 262 - feeding operation
270 - agricultural field methods 271 - straight row 272 - crop residue 273 - contoured 275 - pasture 276 - hayfield

Modifiers for vegetation management. Valid values are 301, 302, or as list, "301, 302".
301 - Planted community 302 - Managed for wildlife

Modifiers for management type. Valid values are 310 to 315, or as a list, e.g. "310, 311, 315".
310 - undefined veg. management 311 - burned 312 - mowed 313 - chemical application 314 - bursh cutting 315 - tree thinning
Modifiers for natural community disturbance types. Valid values are 321 to 329, or as a list, e.g. "321, 323, 326".
Old modifiers for the quality of the natural community. NO LONGER USED.

Modifiers for the quality of the natural community, based on DNR's Natural Heritage Element Occurrence Rank (EOR). Valid values:
A = highest quality B = good quality C = moderate condition D = poor condition NA = native species present in altered/non-native community NN = Altered/non-native community
FLD_LEVEL must be => 3 for A or B ranking FLD_LEVEL must be => 2 for C or D ranking FLD_LEVEL must be => 1 for NA or NN ranking

Purple Loosestrife. Valid values:
0 = unknown, or if field checked, plants not observed 1 = observed, unknown quality 2 = 1 to 5% coverage 3 = 6 to 25% coverage 4 = 26 to 50% coverage 5 = 51 to 75% coverage 6 = 76 to 100% coverage
Modifiers for Tree Species. Valid values 500 to 546 or as a list, "512, 524, 530".
Modifiers for forest dynamics. Valid values 601 to 604.
Modifiers for percentage of tree canopy, numerical range. Valid values 610 to 616.
Modifiers for cover size (average diameter of trees). Valid values 621 to 629.

Modifiers for NWI regimes. Valid values 710 to 716.
710 - Temporarily Flooded (A) 711 - Saturated (B) 712 - Seasonally Flooded (C) 713 - Semipermanently Flooded (F) 714 - Intermittently Exposed (G) 715 - Permanently Flooded (H) 716 - Artificially Flooded (K)

Modifiers for built water features. Valid values 720 to 726.
721 - partially drained/ditched 726 - excavated

Modifiers for wetland features. Valid values 730 to 734.
731 - water feature for stormwater management

Modifiers for stream features. Valid values 740, 741.
740 - stream present 741 - ditch present
Modifiers for spring features. Valid value, 750.
Author of data (interpretation and digitizing). Mandatory field - state "organization, ecologist/digitizer (if different)", e.g. "Dakota County SWCD, D. Holmen"
